&lt;/script&gt;
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://c2.staticflickr.com/6/5607/15777372492_e4ca6e08b1_k.jpg&quot; style=&quot;float:left; height:267px; margin:10px; width:400px&quot; /&gt;We’re hosting our second annual AllSeen Alliance Summit this October 19-21 in Seattle, which means the event is just over a month away!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;With keynotes, a plugfest and three, distinct speaking tracks, we’ve designed this year’s program to cater to every key stakeholder in IoT - whether you’re a business decision maker, operations manager, developer or a technical product manager.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here’s 5 reasons you need to attend:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://allseensummit2015.sched.org/overview/type/business+%2F+product+management?iframe=no&amp;amp;w=i%3A100%3B&amp;amp;sidebar=yes&amp;amp;bg=no#.VfB-9rRdV0h&quot;&gt;Monetizing IoT, Certification, Edge Computing Analytics: &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;These are just a few of the business challenges to consider as the growth rate of connected devices climbs: How can a common framework like AllJoyn create revenue opportunities? How are engineering resources freed up when open source software is leveraged? We’ll hear from service providers, product makers, retailers and others who can share their experience to-date, the obstacles they’re facing, and the innovative solutions they’re finding in an open ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2.&lt;strong&gt; Security. Privacy. Data. Cloud.&lt;/strong&gt; Seems like four reasons in one, right? These aren’t just buzzwords in IoT. These are real issues impeding our ability to move IoT from a term to a major market shift for businesses, industries and consumers. If you’re interested in a technical discussion around cloud gateways or keen to learn how data is managed across AllJoyn devices, services or apps,&lt;strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://events.linuxfoundation.org/events/allseen-alliance-summit/program/schedule&quot;&gt;join the discussion&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. &lt;strong&gt;Networking&lt;/strong&gt;: This is the only industry event where you’ll have access to companies representing every horizontal area of interest in IoT. With 600+ attendees, both members and non-members, from all over the world, you’ll have unlimited opportunities in this 3-day event. Want to talk to product manufacturers or software application developers? What about cloud and data experts? They’re all coming to this event. Learn more about &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://events.linuxfoundation.org/events/allseen-alliance-summit/program/about&quot;&gt;who’s coming&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and how you can collaborate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. &lt;strong&gt;Parents. Chefs. Gardners. Athletes&lt;/strong&gt;. What really matters to consumers when it comes to smart, connected ‘things’? IoT is truly about providing everyone with flexibility and choice, regardless of brand or manufacturer. We’re hosting &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://allseensummit2015.sched.org/type/technical?iframe=no#.VfBrj2RVhBc&quot;&gt;technical talks&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to cover ‘how’ we can realize this potential as well as business tracks that explore ‘what’ we need to do to better reach consumers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://events.linuxfoundation.org/events/allseen-alliance-summit/extend-the-experience/alljoyn-plugfest&quot;&gt;AllJoyn PlugFest:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; See the power of the AllJoyn ecosystem brought to life in two days of hands-on interaction and test sessions. The AllSeen interoperability Plugfest allows you to test your AllJoyn-enabled products with other devices in our private and well-supported environment, with experts on hand to help with issues in real time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;When asked why companies should join and collaborate at this year&#039;s event, Philip DesAutels, AllSeen Alliance senior director, said, “This year’s AllSeen Alliance Summit is going to provide a unique opportunity for any stakeholder in IoT to network and collaborate so that we can work together to overcome the industry’s toughest challenges. From business sessions that allow leaders to brainstorm and troubleshoot industry hot topics like security and big data to hands-on learning labs that explore AllJoyn and products built using the software, everyone has something to gain from attending this event.”&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://events.linuxfoundation.org/events/allseen-alliance-summit/attend/register&quot;&gt;Register now&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;and follow &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/AllSeenSummit?src=hash&quot;&gt;#AllSeenSummit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; for live updates! And for those who didn’t catch us at the 2014 AllSeen Alliance Summit, take a look at this &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RVdmT5Yllp0&amp;amp;list=PL4IDeLjCA5CPnjWo8OET8X0gg4d9F_D-k&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;video&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to see get an idea of what you can expect this year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
