<item>
 <title>Community Blog Series: ThroughTek</title>
 <link>https://identity.allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2015/07/community-blog-series-throughtek</link>
 <description>
		&lt;span class=&quot;a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list&quot; id=&quot;da2a_3&quot;&gt;
			&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_facebook&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_google_plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_dd addtoany_share_save&quot; href=&quot;http://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=https%3A%2F%2Fidentity.allseenalliance.org%2Fnews%2Fblogs%2F2015%2F07%2Fcommunity-blog-series-throughtek&amp;amp;title=Blogs%20-%20AllSeen%20Alliance&quot;&gt; Share&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://i60.tinypic.com/2wfmosj.jpg&quot; style=&quot;float:left; height:150px; margin:5px; width:150px&quot; /&gt;Yuping Tseng, Chief Technology Officer of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.throughtek.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;ThroughTek&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yuping Tseng has over 20 years of experience in software development, internet services, and system administration. He has held various appointments at Hewlett-Packard and Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company, as well as at the University of Illinois. Yuping&#039;s expertise in software and internet industry includes information retrieval, data mining, parallel processing, network communication, web development, mobile applications, cloud services, and cluster management. He currently works with emerging IoT opportunities and machine-to-machine communications, leading a growing team of researchers and developers at ThroughTek to develop complete and comprehensive solutions for IoT industries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why did you join the AllSeen Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.throughtek.com&quot;&gt;ThroughTek&lt;/a&gt; wants to be able to contribute and create opportunities for the Internet of Things (IoT) market by working together across company lines and industries. The AllSeen Alliance addresses the challenges associated with IoT and is working to create unified standards for connected devices. ThroughTek hopes to contribute with our experiences in delivering multimedia solutions for instant file access and video streaming in real-time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does ThroughTek hope to achieve through its participation in the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The AllSeen Alliance provides members with the opportunity to create an open source communications framework to allow products and services to be part of a larger ecosystem. ThroughTek aims to expand its vertical integration to develop strategic services that will improve interoperability and optimize services for products and applications.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What contributions is ThroughTek making to the project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;ThroughTek is working to integrate the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.throughtek.com/features.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kalay cloud platform’s&lt;/a&gt; multimedia module to the AllJoyn framework. This would enable the AllJoyn software framework to support video streaming, push notification services and connectivity over the internet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multimedia Streaming Interface - to enable data transmission of multimedia between AllJoyn devices; and&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kalay Cloud Platform – provides cloud services, ie. data analytics, cloud recording, video streaming, push notification service.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example use case scenarios include:&lt;br /&gt;- Someone arrives at the door and rings the door phone (doorbell with camera installed);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Notification is pushed directly to the homeowner’s smart TV and/or smart phone; and&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Once notification is accepted, live video feed will be delivered to the smart TV and/or smart phone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you describe the Internet of Everything? Can you help us understand how our homes and business might function 10 years from now because of AllJoyn and the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The adoption of IoT is increasing with the number of connected devices, which is estimated to outnumber the human population three to one by 2020. This will transform and define new means for the way humans and machines interact with each other. Long-term collaboration will not only make products more intelligent, but it will create a learning ecosystem with objects working together. Greater connectivity and ultimate functionality through ubiquitous networking of the Internet will create highly personalized and often predictive connected experiences in smart environments.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why is open source software and collaborative development important for advancing the Internet of Everything?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Open source software and collaborative development is important because it focuses on building foundations for IoT, while also creating new market opportunities that allow companies to develop compelling products and/or services to drive enhancements for consumer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The IoT ecosystem is vast; interoperability and the ability to embrace other APIs, applications and partner services will ultimately help to deliver more compelling products and services. Open source software allows businesses to save time and money on development while reducing time to bring IoT products to the market. In the end, open source technology benefits everyone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will the work of the AllSeen Alliance impact the industry?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The AllSeen Alliance will contribute software and engineering resources to create an open software framework that enables hardware makers, service providers and software developers to create interoperable devices and services. As IoT gains broader adoption, businesses will shift from products to outcome-based services, competing on the ability to deliver measurable results with value-added applications. Ultimately, a unified standard that can be used across different devices, applications and platforms will help the IoT market innovate and develop products to be integrated seamlessly into our lives.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
 <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2015 07:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
