    &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.kii.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Kii Logo&quot; src=&quot;http://status.kii.com/images/logo.png&quot; style=&quot;float:left; height:127px; margin:7px; width:200px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.kii.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kii&lt;/a&gt; is focused on addressing the high-performance demands of innovation in the connected world with an end-to-end cloud platform optimized for the IoT. Since 2007, our organizational DNA has been in serving the world’s largest carriers with connectivity, scale, stability and performance. By extending our platform and global business expertise to device manufactures and startups, we help today’s disruptive technologies become tomorrow’s household names. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why did you join the AllSeen Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kii is providing cloud backend for mobile applications and IoT device solutions (BaaS).   Our offering includes device management, device analytics, user management, data management, push notification, geo location, end user behavior analytics, A/B Testing etc.  Kii&#039;s main customers are device manufactures, mobile application developers, service providers such as carrier, cable TV companies and Internet service providers.   We believe the AllSeen Alliance’s approach is good and something we feel strongly about being a part of. Because we have a partnership with potential IoT solution distribution channels, we believe that we can help ensure distribution of AllSeen-enabled devices.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does your company hope to achieve through its participation in the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Through our participation within the Alliance, we hope to create compelling solutions for end users.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What contributions is your company making, or is considering making, to the project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since we have expertise in a cloud, a capability of focus for AllJoyn, we would like to help develop a business model(s) using cloud service for AllJoyn-enabled devices.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you describe the Internet of Everything? Can you help us understand how our homes and business might function 10 years from now because of AllJoyn and the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’ve been talking about the Internet of Everything (IoE) for almost 10 years now, but it’s only recently that we’ve seen a huge boom in the space. The AllSeen Alliance allows more people to jump in to create very interesting solutions and applications. By having open protocol and APIs on IoE devices, AllJoyn will create a open and interoperable ecosystem like to what we’ve seen in proprietary ecosystems like Apple and Google’s smartphones.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why is open source software and collaborative development important for advancing the Internet of Everything?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;My previous experience as a board member of the Infrared Data Association (IrDA) helped me understand how difficult it is to ensure interoperability. I understand the value of creating a specification on top of an open source framework.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will the work of the AllSeen Alliance impact the industry in the short term? In the long term?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is strong momentum behind the AllSeen Alliance, especially in the growth and scope of its member companies. Members include companies that provide all of the necessary IoE components. The Alliance will continue to grow and will quickly expand to cover many user cases. The growth of the Alliance will benefit end users by  providing solutions that are easier to use, interoperable and cost effective.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, we believe that the Alliance’s open source developers will grow into a huge community and unbelievable innovation will happen within it.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
