<item>
 <title>AllJoyn 15.04 Available for Download</title>
 <link>https://identity.allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2015/05/alljoyn-1504-available-download</link>
 <description>
		&lt;span class=&quot;a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list&quot; id=&quot;da2a_7&quot;&gt;
			&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_facebook&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_google_plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_dd addtoany_share_save&quot; href=&quot;http://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=https%3A%2F%2Fidentity.allseenalliance.org%2Fnews%2Fblogs%2F2015%2F05%2Falljoyn-1504-available-download&amp;amp;title=Blogs%20-%20AllSeen%20Alliance&quot;&gt; Share&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;AllJoyn 15.04 is &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/developers/download&quot;&gt;available for download&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The fourth major release of AllJoyn since the Alliance was formed, 15.04 builds on the rich, commercially deployed AllJoyn foundation to deliver higher performance, extended scalability and enhanced security features. These enhancements strengthen AllJoyn’s capabilities in consumer, enterprise and industrial scenarios. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Features for AllJoyn 15.04 &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.allseenalliance.org/cgit/core/alljoyn.git/plain/alljoyn_core/docs/ReleaseNotes.txt?h=RB15.04&quot;&gt;Standard Library&lt;/a&gt; include:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Property cache feature which adds a simple, optional cache to ProxyBusObject that keeps track of property values as received in GetProperty, GetAllProperties calls and PropertiesChanged signals;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;​Support for X.509 ECDSA digital certificates, which replace the X.509 RSA certificates;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Remove excessive name transfer for all sessions. This limits the names exchanged to just the routing node and host/joiners as a part of an effort to reduce network traffic;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Observer Functionality: this feature simplifies interface based discovery of bus objects by filtering such that listeners only trigger if something relevant has changed in an About Announcement. It also enables automatic session setup and takes care of proxy bus object creation and life-cycle management;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;It is now possible to build for Android without requiring OpenSSL from the platform, this greatly simplifies making Android builds;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add to About C API: a second announce_using_datalistener method was added that takes as argument an AboutDataListener instead of AboutData;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add support for detecting idle RNs allowing the RN to shut down automatically if no LNs have used its services for a while; and&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support for iOS 8.1.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Features for AllJoyn 15.04 &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.allseenalliance.org/cgit/core/ajtcl.git/tree/ReleaseNotes.txt?h=RB15.04&quot;&gt;Thin Library&lt;/a&gt; include:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Allow the setting of the UNMARSHAL_TIMEOUT. This gives applications explicit control over how long unmarshalling waits for new input before giving up;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;AJTCL Router Selection (ASACORE-803). TC applications now use the rank advertised by the router to select the most desirable router;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support for X.509 ECDSA digital certificates, which replace the X.509 RSA certificates;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;AJTCL adds information string to reply messages. This feature duplicates the standard library API functionality that allows information to be added to a reply message;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add support for specifying NVRAM file location on Windows; and&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;EXPERIMENTAL: UDP Transport for TC &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; RN connections. Thin Client to Routing Node version of a UDP-based transport.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;This release of AllJoyn is validated to run on the following platforms:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Linux Ubuntu&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Android JellyBean&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Windows 7, 8.1 and 10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;iOS&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;OSX&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;OpenWRT&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The AllSeen Alliance has surpassed 160 member organizations invested in the AllJoyn open source software project. Diversity in members collaborating across industries creates richer, more stable and highly scalable code. We encourage you to join us and further advance AllJoyn as the simple and open technology for the Internet of Everything. &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/developers/download&quot;&gt;Download the code&lt;/a&gt;, join the conversation and get started today!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
 <pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2015 17:15:45 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>AllSeen Alliance</dc:creator>
