 <title>Community Blog Series: Weaved</title>
 <link>https://identity.allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2015/05/community-blog-series-weaved</link>
 <description>
		&lt;span class=&quot;a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list&quot; id=&quot;da2a_8&quot;&gt;
			&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_facebook&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_google_plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_dd addtoany_share_save&quot; href=&quot;http://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=https%3A%2F%2Fidentity.allseenalliance.org%2Fnews%2Fblogs%2F2015%2F05%2Fcommunity-blog-series-weaved&amp;amp;title=Blogs%20-%20AllSeen%20Alliance&quot;&gt; Share&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Weaved logo&quot; src=&quot;http://www.safelogic.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Weaved_LogoResize.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border-style:solid; border-width:0px; float:left; height:166px; margin:2px; width:250px&quot; /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.weaved.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Weaved &lt;/a&gt;is start-up based in downtown Palo Alto, founded by serial entrepreneurs with a deep background in TCP/IP networking and cloud services.  The Company is angel funded and backed by some of the top investors for both networking and cloud service companies.  Weaved is committed to the vision of making it possible for anyone to create their own Internet of Things applications, to realize the Internet of Things for Everyone.  Today, the Company offers a fully capable, software-only, hardware-agnostic platform along with drop-in services, to easily enable sophisticated users and developers to add Internet of Things capability to any already networked products.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why did Weaved join the AllSeen Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As long time participants in the Internet connected market, we realized the need for a baseline interoperability standard. The Alliance’s vision of providing an open source framework, combined with the quality and number of initial members, prompted us to join as a founding member.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does Weaved hope to achieve through its participation in the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We hope to become a participant in the formation and establishment of the Internet of Things ecosystem. Through participation in the Alliance, we believe we will be exposed to a wide range of different industries and like-minded providers, with who we can collaborate and partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What contributions is Weaved making to the project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To date our participation has been in thought leadership and marketing. Going forward, we expect to be active in both the marketing and technical aspects of the project as it relates to end-user usability, especially where legacy interfaces can leverage the Alliance&#039;s work to add new &quot;connected&quot; features.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you describe the Internet of Everything? Can you help us understand how our homes and business might function 10 years from now because of AllJoyn and the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We believe that 10 years from now, no businesses or product economies will exist that don&#039;t leverage the Internet of Everything. Initially this will involve connectivity and control mostly via mobile devices, evolving to machine learning and big data analysis for user experience benefits, and ultimately, to transformation and optimization of industries as a result of the cumulative effect of the collected information.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why is open source software and collaborative development important for advancing the Internet of Everything?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Technology and demand have outpaced development cycles during the Internet age. Much like the Internet infrastructure, open source will be the only means to allow for the rapid deployment of &#039;best practices&#039; and interoperable standards. Without an open source solution, the industry will be doomed to siloed point solutions – characterized by consumers who are resistant to adopt at a mass market level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will the work of the AllSeen Alliance impact the industry in the short term? What about in the long term? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Near term the Alliance can impact existing network-enabled point solutions, by easily allowing them to become Internet-connected and industry interoperable. Over time, much like Internet protocol standards, the work that the Alliance is doing will provide the assurance of a baseline set of capabilities, ensuring multi vendor compatibility and capability.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
