  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://organicresponse.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Organic Response logo&quot; src=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/sites/default/files/member_logos/logo_organic.png&quot; style=&quot;float:left; height:140px; margin:3px; width:200px&quot; /&gt;Organic Response&lt;/a&gt; is a sensor-based lighting control system that uses distributed intelligence to maximize energy savings and occupancy comfort. By utilizing distributed intelligence, it has delivered a plug and play system that requires no wiring or commissioning to deliver simple but sophisticated lighting control. A key aspect of the technology is the smart sensor network, called the Occupancy Information Cloud, that is created when Organic Response enabled lighting is installed. This enables each light fixture to be continuously aware of what is happening within the broader network, and as such is ideally suited to a fast and exciting transition into the Internet of Everything.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why did you join the AllSeen Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There were a number of reasons for this. Firstly we wanted to tap in to the community in general and gain an insight to what people are doing in the space. We were obviously keen to contribute to and shape the development of the software to suit our idea of where we thought IoT should go, and of course utilise the open source code that is being generated.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does your company hope to achieve through its participation in the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We hope to dramatically speed up the development of IoT and our participation in this exciting new technology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What contributions is your company making, or is considering making, to the project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We bring our unique method of collecting occupancy and other sensor information within buildings for the ultimate goal of resource efficiency - whether the resource is energy, or real estate. By sharing this rich information with other devices, systems and people we allow all of them to operate as smartly as our lighting control.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you describe the Internet of Everything? Can you help us understand how our homes and business might function 10 years from now because of AllJoyn and the Alliance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Internet of Everything is really about collecting and sharing information to make smarter decisions, and operate more efficiently. Whether it is machine to machine, or to people if we have the right data at the right time we can transform the way energy is consumed and resources are utilised. If we get this right everything and everyone will become so much smarter. Alljoyn has a crucial role to play to ensure we get it right, and get it right at the right time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
